Tim,

I don&#39;t know why &#39;stoichiometric_solid&#39; is not being recognized, unless 
you are using an older version of Cantera.  This used to be called 
&#39;pure_solid&#39;, so you might try that if you are using a version prior to 
1.5.4.

There are a few other problems with your cti file: the elements line 
has a missing quote,  the density is missing (required for 
&#39;stoichiometric_solid&#39;), and there is no species specified in the file. 
If I modify your input file as follows

-------------------------------------------------
stoichiometric_solid(name = &#39;Pt111&#39;,
                      elements = &#39;E O Pt&#39;,
                      species = &#39;all&#39;,
                      density = 1.0
                      )

species(name = &#39;Pt(s)&#39;,
         atoms = &#39;Pt:1&#39;,
         thermo = const_cp()
         )
-----------------------------------------------

then it works for me in MATLAB:

 &gt;&gt; p = importPhase(&#39;pt.cti&#39;)

        temperature                  300  K
        pressure                  101325  Pa
        density                        1  kg/m^3
        mean mol. weight          195.08  amu

                            X                 Y
                      -------------     ------------
              Pt(s)   1.000000e+00     1.000000e+00

 &gt;&gt;

See if this works for you. If it does not, and you are running version 
1.5.4, let me know.

Dave



